  • public class ClassDeclaration
extends InstanceDeclaration
    Declaration extension that represents the declaration of a class node type. See decodeStatement(Node, String, Location, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static ClassDeclaration decodeStatement(Node parent,
                               java.lang.String statement,
                               Location location,
                               boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into a ClassDeclaration, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.

        Example inputs include:
        • public class ClassName
        • private static class ClassName
        • public abstract class ClassName
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        statement - The statement to translate into a ClassDeclaration if possible.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a ClassDeclaration.
